<HEADLINE>
Dollar, gold rise
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar rose against most other major
currencies in European trading Wednesday morning. Gold rose .
	   Dollar rates compared with late Tuesday:
	   _1.6705 German marks, up from 1.6695
	   _115.20 Japanese yen, down from 115.38
	   _1.3685 Swiss francs, up from 1.3620
	   _5.6021 French francs, up from 5.5952
	   _1.8823 Dutch guilders, up from 1.8815
	   _1,653.86 Italian lire, up from 1,652.10
	   _1.5520 Canadian dollars, up from 1.5512
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6738 down from dlrs
1.6832.
	   Gold dealers in London fixed a recommended price of dlrs 286.80
bid per troy ounce at midmorning, up from dlrs 287.00 on Tuesday.
	   In Zurich the bid price was dlrs 287.15, up from dlrs 287.00.
	   Gold was unchanged in Hong Kong at dlrs 286.95.
	   Silver rates were not available.
	   (acw)
</TEXT>
