<SLUG> BC-Germany-Robbery </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Millions stolen in armored car holdup in Germany
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) _ A gang that held up an armored car
outside a bank near Frankfurt made off with millions of marks
(dollars), police said Wednesday.
	   Initial reports after the robbery Tuesday outside a Sparkasse
branch in Seligenstadt were that the four armed robbers, one with a
Kalashnikov submachine gun, had made off with a ``six-figure'' sum.
	   But police spokesman Georg Grebner said the actual amount was
much higher, ``in the millions.'' He declined to be more specific.
	   The transport company's insurance offered a 100,000 mark (dlrs
61,000) reward for information leading to the capture of the
robbers.
 &UR; (pfg-dkt)
