<SLUG> BC-Israel-Lebanon,0161 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Israeli soldier killed in Lebanon, apparently by friendly fire
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By SARI BASHI &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ An Israeli soldier was killed and two were
wounded before dawn Wednesday when one Israeli army unit mistakenly
opened fire on another in southern Lebanon, radio reports said.
	   The army confirmed the casualties and said it was investigating
whether friendly fire was the cause.
	   The dead soldier was identified as Staff Sgt. Ohad Zach, 19,
from the northern village of Nofit.
	   Israel radio and Israel army radio said the incident occurred
when two units of soldiers on patrol lost contact with each other,
and one unit fired on the other.
	   The shooting occurred in Israel's self-styled security zone.
Israel has occupied the zone since 1985 to prevent cross-border
guerrilla attacks. With rising casualties, public pressure has been
mounting to withdraw Israel's 2,000 soldiers from Lebanon.
</TEXT>
