<SLUG> BC-India-Tiger,0134 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Prime Minister Vajpayee choses Indian tiger for greeting cards
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NEW DELHI, India (AP) _ Indian Prime Minister Atal Bihari
Vajpayee is sending out New Year's greeting cards featuring two
Bengal tigers to promote efforts to rescue the endangered cat.
	   The gesture comes in the silver jubilee year of Project Tiger, a
nationwide effort to preserve the forests where tigers live.
	   ``When the government shows commitment to wildlife at the
highest level, the message goes down well,'' said Samar Singh,
secretary-general of the World Wildlife Fund-India, quoted by the
Times of India newspaper Wednesday.
	   Nearly 60 percent of the world's 7,000 tigers live in India.
They are threatened by poachers seeking their hide or bones, which
are used in Chinese medicines.
</TEXT>
