<SLUG> BC-Italy-Prisoner Recaptured </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Three-time prison escapee captured
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MILAN, Italy (AP) _ A convicted murderer who escaped from prison
here on Christmas was captured Wednesday, the Italian news agency
ANSA reported.
	   Joan Ursut, who in the past had escaped twice from Swedish
prisons, used a knotted bed sheet Friday to shimmy out of a Milan
prison window and to brief freedom.
	   Fog had hampered the immediate search.
	   ANSA reported that the 40-year-old Romanian, who has a 21-year
sentence for the murder of an Italian gangster, was arrested by
Italian police near Modena, a town about 170 km (110 miles) from
Milan.
	   (srj-fd)
