<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Russia-Capsized Barge </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Four bodies found on capsized barge in Russian Far East
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Rescue workers on Wednesday found the bodies of
four border guards who drowned when a supply barge capsized and
sank in icy waters in Russia's Far East, a news report said.
	   One more body had been found Tuesday and four crew members were
still missing and feared dead.
	   Of the 11 men who were on the barge when it went down, only two
have been rescued. They survived by hanging onto the barge's hull
until rescuers found them, according to the Federal Border Guards
in Moscow.
	   The four bodies found Wednesday had been inside the barge's
control room, the Interfax news agency said. Workers were not able
to locate them earlier because poor weather slowed down rescue
efforts.
	   The search for the remaining bodies has been temporarily halted
because of high winds, Interfax said.
	   The barge, carrying supplies to a border guard post, overturned
and sank Sunday as it passed through a hard-to-navigate section of
the Kamchatka river, located on the Kamchatka peninsula about 6,700
kilometers (4,200 miles) east of Moscow.
	   (nw/gm) 	   
</TEXT>
