<HEADLINE>
Child killed in diplomatic car crash
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SOFIA, Bulgaria (AP) _ A car bearing Mongolian diplomats skidded
off an icy road in northern Bulgaria and crashed into a pile of
sand Wednesday, killing a 2-year-old passenger, police said.
	   Another occupant, a woman, was reported hospitalized in a coma.
	   Police said the driver was said to be speeding at the time of
the accident near Byala, 250 kilometers (160 miles) northeast of
the capital Sofia.
	   No other details were immediately released.
