<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Romania-Fake Hero </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
False revolution hero arrested for fraud in Romania
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) _ A man who coaxed thousands of dollars
out of Romanian companies by evoking the name of a hero of the 1989
revolution has been arrested for suspected fraud, police said
Wednesday.
	   Catalin Alistar, 23, has been obtaining money and free services
for two years from companies that thought they were dealing with
the ``Gavroche'' of revolution fame, officer Mariana Apostol said.
	   The real Gavroche is Florin Vieru. Only a child during the
events that toppled communism, Vieru marched on the streets of the
capital waving a revolutionary flag. His picture appeared in the
media worldwide. He is now a taxi driver.
	   Alistar used to call managers of different companies pretending
to be a state secretary and saying someone nicknamed Gavroche would
come on his behalf to collect.
	   He was caught by police this week after receiving money from a
company in Focsani, 175 kilometers (110 miles) northeast of the
capital Bucharest.
	   Alistar admitted misleading even the Moldovan Interior Ministry,
which arranged for his accommodations and gave him presents during
a visit last year.
	   ``He managed to get tens of million lei (thousands of dollars)
from more than 20 companies in two years by appealing to their
naive patriotic feelings,'' Apostol said.
	   (mc/dc)
</TEXT>
