YEMEN: WRAP - APTN is chasing pictures of survivors from Yemen where
three kidnapped Britons and an Australian were killed in a police
raid. (Pictures and soundbites will be f-l-a-s-hed as soon as
possible/please look out for advisories) In house, we already have a
still of one of the British victims, comments from his employers and
reaction from Australian government officials. (Wrap first run 1600
Europe)
-----
BELGIUM: EURO - On the momentous occasion of the launch of the
European Union's new currency,  a euro sign will be projected on an
old EC building in Brussels. (First Run expected after 1730)
----
FRANCE: BOURSE - As the countdown continues to the Euro launch, APTN
will have coverage of the bourse. It is the last day of trading
before share prices are converted to the euro. (First Run Expected
after 1730)
----
RUSSIA: WOMEN'S JAIL - Control of the prison system is being
transferred to the Justice Ministry in hopes of improving conditions
- especially for women who represent 40,000 of Russia's 1 million
prisoners. APTN travelled to Mozhaisk to see how some of the jail's
1,100 female inmates are coping. (First Run Expected Europe Late
1600g)
----
COLOMBIA: BULLFIGHT - A young Spanish bullfighter was gored by a
530 kilogram (1,168 pound) bull in front of thousands of spectators and
survived. APTN has pictures of the bull piercing the
fighter's neck, lower pelvis and right leg before horrified
spectators. (First Run Expected After 1700)
----
CUBA: FUNERAL - Thousands of Cubans have paid their last respects to
Tania the Guerrilla, the only woman to fight with legendary
leftist rebel Ernesto "Che" Guevara on his last
revolutionary mission in 1967. APTN has pictures from the funeral.
(First Run Expected Europe Late 1600)
----
MEXICO: ARREST - Two Mexican Indians have been arrested in the
slaying of an American journalist because they didn't want their
picture taken. The camera-shy suspects are charged with strangling
the photographer and later stealing his camera and belongings.
(First Run Europe Late 1600)
----
US: BABIES  - Parents Nkem Chukwu and Iyke Louis Udobi are expected
to give a news conference as they finally leave for home. (First Run
Europe Late 1600)
----
