at President Bill Clinton's impeachment trial, which could begin
Jan. 7 under a blueprint that Senate Majority Leader Trent Lott
proposed to Democrats. US-CLINTON-IMPEACHMENT.
	   ALSO:
	   ISRAEL-LEBANON. An Israeli soldier was killed and two were
wounded before dawn Wednesday when one Israeli army unit mistakenly
opened fire on another in southern Lebanon, an army commander said.
	   NETHERLANDS-UNWELCOME REFUGEES. Protesters accused a group of
rich residents of setting up a ``new apartheid'' by buying a
disused hospital for millions of guilders (dlrs) to prevent asylum
seekers being housed there.
	   GERMANY-SPY. Despite sharp criticism from conservatives, the
former East German communists held fast Wednesday to their plan to
hire a convicted spy who betrayed NATO secrets during the Cold War.
	   INDONESIA-SOLDIERS KILLED. A mob of 200 villagers, some armed
with machetes, torture and kill eight Indonesian soldiers after
stopping a public bus. On Wednesday, rioters in the same area
attack a police station and burn two police cars
