within the Kosovo Albanian camp should be resolved and that
``reality requires a consensus of all Kosovo Albanian factions.''
	   U.S. mediators in the conflict have been trying to unite Kosovo
Albanian factions, a prerequisite for any fruitful direct peace
talks with the Serbian government.
	   Ajeti also said the ethnic Albanians still expect NATO
intervention against the government troops fighting to prevent the
secession.
