<HEADLINE>
Air France plane loses wheel, makes emergency landing
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: UPDATES with details on wheel, quote from Air France official &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LYON, France (AP) _ An Air France plane on a regular domestic
flight between Lyon and Nantes lost a wheel after takeoff Wednesday
but made an emergency landing safely, the Lyon airport said.
	   The Boeing 737-300 plane, with 59 people on board, landed at
Lyon-Satolas airport about 10:20 a.m. (0920 GMT), the airport said.
	   The flight, AF7863, was to have flown from Lyon to the western
French city of Nantes. The rear left wheel of the six-wheel plane
fell off just after takeoff.
	   ``The risk was minimal,'' said Eric Samuel, an Air France
official at the airport. ``It was much less serious than if it had
been a nose wheel.''
