<HEADLINE>
Elke Sommer wins verdict against Zsa Zsa Gabor's husband
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NUREMBERG, Germany (AP) _ German actress Elke Sommer won the
latest round Wednesday in a long-running war of words with Zsa Zsa
Gabor and her German husband, Prince Frederic von Anhalt.
	   A Bavarian court rejected an appeal from the prince, who had
been ordered by a lower court to stop going around telling people
that Sommer had once called all German men ``pigs.''
	   But since Sommer could not definitively prove that she had not
made the disputed statement, the court did not order von Anhalt to
make a full retraction.
	   The three have been spatting for years. According to Sommer, the
bad blood began after she remarked once that Gabor had a large
butt.
	   In 1992, a Los Angeles jury ordered Hungarian-born Gabor and von
Anhalt, a former Munich champagne dealer and Gabor's eighth
husband, to pay Sommer dlrs 2.5 million in damages for describing
her as a haggard Hollywood has-been.
