<HEADLINE>
WIndies bowler Walsh is doubtful for next cricket test v. SAfrica
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   DURBAN, South Africa (AP) _ A hamstring injury has left West
Indian star bowler Courtney Walsh doubtful for the next test match
against South Africa, team officials said Wednesday.
	   Walsh injured his left hamstring Tuesday while fielding on the
last day of the third test. The series, which South Africa leads
3-0, moves to Cape Town on Saturday.
	   Curtly Ambrose, suffering from fluid on the knee, also is not in
top form but he could still play.
	   ``We're awaiting the doctor's report,'' said West Indies manager
Clive Lloyd. ``Mr. Walsh, according to the doctor, has a slight
tear of the hamstring. I doubt whether he will play,'' Lloyd said.
	   The West Indians are struggling on the field. They lost by four
wickets at the Wanderers stadium in Johannesburg, by 178 runs at
St. George's in Port Elizabeth and by nine wickets at Kingsmead
here.
	   The last time a South African team has led 4-0 was against
Australia. No South African team has won a series 5-0.
