<HEADLINE>
India's controversial navy chief fired, defense official
</HEADLINE>
transferred &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   NEW DELHI, India (AP) _ India's controversial navy chief, who
failed to promote officials recommended by the Defense Ministry,
was fired Wednesday following a long-running spat with top
bureaucrats.
	   ``The government has terminated the services of Chief of Navy
Staff Admiral (Vishnu) Bhagwat,'' an official statement said. The
dismissal took effect immediately.
	   Vice Adm. Sushil Kumar, who was in charge of the navy's
operations in south India, was named the new naval chief.
	   The government also transferred Ajit Kumar, the top official in
the Defense Ministry involved in the controversy, to the industrial
policy and promotion department.
	   The decision came following acrimonious exchange of letters
between Bhagwat and the Defense Ministry. Bhagwat was unavailable
for comment.
