<HEADLINE>
Share prices drop at year's end of trading in London
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP _ Share prices fell on the London Stock Exchange on
Wednesday.
	   In a shortened session, the Financial Time-Stock Exchange
100-share index of blue-chip stocks fell 58.9 points, or 0.99
percent, to 5,882.6. Provisional volume was 171 million shares
compared with 261.6 million on Tuesday.
	   The FTSE 100 ended the year up 14.5 percent from the end of
1997, after posting a year's low of 4,599.2 on Oct. 8 and an
all-time high of 6,183.7 on July 20.
	   Dealers said the Jan. 1 launch of the single European currency
is unlikely to affect the London stock market. Britain is not
taking part yet in the currency, the euro.
	   The market reopens Jan. 4.
