the Egyptian as Osama al-Masri. In Cairo, Egyptian security sources
said the name was the alias of a wanted Islamic extremist. They
refused to give his real name.
	   British newspapers accused Yemeni authorities of intervening
prematurely. The Daily Mail asked on the front page, ``Did our
