r f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Switzerland-Inflation     12-30 0174
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Switzerland-Inflation </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Switzerland reports zero inflation rate
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) _ Switzerland has won the battle
against inflation, with a zero rate of price increase recorded for
1998, according to official figures issued Wednesday.
	   It was the lowest rate since 1959 and marked the fifth straight
year that the government had achieved its goal of price stability _
an inflation rate of less than 2 percent.
	   With the Swiss economy in good shape, the country's central bank
has said there is little chance of deflation or recession in the
foreseeable future.
	   Economists predict that an increase in value-added tax from Jan.
1 will lead to a rise in the consumer price index of around 0.5
percent early next year but have said significant price hikes are
unlikely.
	   The December consumer price index was unchanged from November
and decreased 0.2 percent year on year, the federal statistical
office said. This was partly thanks to falling gasoline prices and
personal computer prices.
 &UR; (cn)
</TEXT>
