w2885 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Netherlands-ChildPorn     12-30 0204
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Netherlands-Child Porn </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Government announces formation of national child pornography
</HEADLINE>
investigation network

<TEXT>
	   THE HAGUE, Netherlands (AP) _ The government will spend one
million guilders (dlrs 532,000) next year setting up a nationwide
police network dedicated to investigating child pornography, Dutch
Justice Minister Benk Korthals announced Wednesday.
	   The announcement follows a number of high-profile child sex
cases in the Netherlands since the summer when an international
pedophile ring's headquarters was discovered in a seaside
apartment.
	   Korthals plans to set up special child porn teams within police
forces across the country which will be coordinated from a national
center with its own public prosecutor. Currently, regional police
forces do not routinely exchange information on child porn
investigations.
	   The new approach also aims at simplifying probes into child
pornography spread on the Internet by setting up permanent
surveillance of Internet sites where pedophiles exchange child
pornographic images.
	   Korthals also announced that the government plans to raise the
penalty for employing child prostitutes in the nation's brothels
from one to six years.
	   (mc) 	   
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
