<HEADLINE>
Kidnappers of wealthy lawyer escape with ransom
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LAUSANNE, Switzerland (AP) _ Swiss police are hunting for three
kidnappers who seized a wealthy lawyer and escaped with 500,000
Swiss francs (dlrs 368,000) in ransom.
	   The hostage, 26-year-old Stephane Lagonico, was freed Dec. 23 as
he was being moved by car. He had been overpowered by four men two
days earlier while getting into his own vehicle in Lausanne.
	   Authorities only released details Wednesday. They said eight
people had been arrested but the three Swiss ringleaders remained
on the run.
	   Lagonico's parents paid out 500,000 francs in agreement with
police to trap the kidnappers, who initially demanded 5 million
francs (dlrs 3.7 million) ransom.
	   The Lagonico family is well-known and influential in the
French-speaking part of Switzerland.
