<SLUG> BC-Italy-Uganda Raid </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Missionaries: Ugandan rebels raid town, killing 3, kidnapping
</HEADLINE>
dozens &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ROME, Italy (AP) _ Ugandan rebels raided a town in the north of
that country, killing three people, kidnapping up to 40 and
stealing supplies, the Italian missionary news service said
Wednesday.
	   The news service, Misna, cited missionary sources in the central
African country.
	   The Lord's Resistance Army carried out the attack on the town of
Morulem on Tuesday night, Misna said.
	   It sacked missionaries' buildings and the clinic of a
missionary-run lepers' hospital, the news service said.
	   Women and children were among the residents abducted, the news
service said.
	   While the adults may have been taken simply to carry the loot,
missionaries feared the young people had been taken to serve as
slaves, it said.
	   The Lord's Resistance Army is waging a 12-year-old insurgency in
northwestern Uganda. Its fighters frequently abduct children and
teen-agers to carry their goods, fight their skirmishes, and
provide them with sex.
	   (ek) 	   
