<SLUG> BC-Uzbekistan-Officers Killed </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Six die in clashes between police and gunmen in Central Asia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A gang of armed men killed three police officers
in Uzbekistan and then tried to flee into neighboring Turkmenistan,
killing three border officers who tried to stop them, a news agency
reported Wednesday.
	   One suspect was later arrested in Uzbekistan, and two other
suspects were identified but not captured, Interfax said, quoting
the Turkmen National Security Committee.
	   The presidents of the two Central Asian countries ordered the
creation of a joint police task force to investigate the crimes.
	   According to authorities, the first shooting occurred Tuesday
when Uzbek police stopped a group of armed men in the Khorezm
region of Uzbekistan, which lies on the Turkmen border.
	   After killing the three officers, the gunmen tried to enter
Turkmenistan at the Gazodzhak checkpoint. In the resulting clash,
two Turkmen border guards and one customs officer died, authorities
said.
	   It was not clear when the second shootout took place, or why the
men had been stopped by police in the first place.
	   (ml)
</TEXT>
