<HEADLINE>
Three killed by explosion of household gas container in Ukraine
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ A household gas container exploded
Wednesday in western Ukraine, killing three people and injuring
three, officials said.
	   The blast occurred at a store also serving as a village cafe in
Lashkivka, a settlement in the Chernivtsi region, regional
administration head Teofil Bauer said, according to the UNIAN news
agency.
	   The administration will provide financial aid to the victims'
families, said Bauer.
	   Accidents involving household gas containers and pipes claim
dozens of lives each year in the former Soviet republic.
