<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Dugarry </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
French striker Dugarry turns down move to Juventus
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MARSEILLE, France (AP) _ Marseille striker Christophe Dugarry
said Wednesday he has decided to turn down a lucrative offer to
move to Italy's Juventus.
	   ``It's been a difficult decision to take,'' Dugarry, 26, told a
news conference. ``I want to stay because I feel good here. The
fans want me to stay, so I'm going to prolong this adventure with
them.''
	   Italian news reports said Juventus had offered dlrs 8 million
for Dugarry, who was a member of France's World Cup-winning squad,
and that a deal was imminent.
	   Juventus coach Marcello Lippi, who watched Dugarry score the
winning goal in a recent match against Lens, has been looking for a
replacement for long-term injury victim Alessandro Del Piero.
	   Dugarry said he spoke on the phone to Juventus' French star
Zinedine Zidane before making his mind up.
	   ``He said: stay at Marseille if that's what you want,'' Dugarry
said. ``Then he said he hoped I help win the French championship.''
	   (parf-ip)
</TEXT>
