<SLUG> BC-Australia-Balloon Quest-Details,0211 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Team Re/Max hopes to be first to fly around the world in balloon
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: Tentative launch time is 1930 GMT Dec. 31 &QL; 
 &UR; With Australia-Balloon Quest &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ALICE SPRINGS, Australia (AP) _ Some details of Team Re/Max
International's attempt to be the first to fly around the world in
a balloon:
	   _Balloon material: Thin, clear polyethylene, of a type used by
NASA in scientific unmanned flights.
	   _Balloon size: About 460 ft. (139 meters) in diameter, 700 feet
(210 meters) high at ``full float.''
	   _Lifting gas: Helium.
	   _Gondola: Similar to a pressurized space capsule.
	   _Crew: Three pilots _ Dave Liniger of Denver, Colorado; Bob
Martin of Albuquerque, New Mexico; John Wallington of Canberra,
Australia.
	   _Launch site: Alice Springs, Australia.
	   _Landing site: Somewhere in Outback Australia.
	   _Flight route: Westerly, following the Tropic of Capricorn.
	   _Cruising altitude: 130,000 ft. (39,600 meters), in the
stratosphere.
	   _Additional Goals: The team hopes to break the altitude record
for a manned balloon flight of 113,740 feet (34,668 meters), and
the manned-balloon flight distance record of 12,600 miles (20276.79
kilometers) set by Chicago millionaire balloonist Steve Fossett.
</TEXT>
