<SLUG> BC-Yugoslavia-Kosovo, UPDATE </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Milosevic: 1999 should bring about political solution for Kosovo
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) _ In a New Year's message broadcast
Wednesday on Serbia's state-run television, Yugoslav president
Slobodan Milosevic said that he expected 1999 to bring about a
political solution for Kosovo.
	   Milosevic's end-of-the-year message, read on prime-time evening
news on Serbian Television, envisaged a ``multi-ethnic Kosovo,
based on the principles of equality for all.''
	   ``No one must be favorized _ not the Serbs, but not the
Albanians either,'' the message said..
	   The message summarized 1998 as particularly difficult since
``pressures'' on the country were ``strongest ever.'' But these
pressures ``united all citizens and parties in a determination to
defend ... the country's integrity,'' said the statement.
	   Milosevic said any future efforts to bring about independence
for the Albanian-majority province of Kosovo will ``come up against
the will of the people'' of Yugoslavia.
	   (kk/gj)
</TEXT>
