<HEADLINE>
Army gets their camera back
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MELBOURNE, Australia (AP) _ A video camera stolen from members
of the English cricket supporters' Barmy Army has been recovered by
detectives at a pawn shop and was returned Thursday to its grateful
owner.
	   The camera, which contained footage of the English cricket fans
following their team all over the world, was stolen from a
Melbourne hotel where the four fans were staying.
	   They were in Melbourne for the fourth cricket test between
England and Australia.
	   The camera was recovered by Dealers Squad detectives at a pawn
shop on Tuesday. A detective saw the camera in a bag, checked the
film and recognized the Barmy Army t-shirts with their distinctive
Union Jacks. (djp) 	   
