<HEADLINE>
Who's in on the single currency and who's out
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With The Euro &QL; 
 &UR; By The Associated Press &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   Eleven European Union countries are joining the euro: Austria,
Belgium, Finland, France, Germany, Ireland, Italy, Luxembourg, the
Netherlands, Portugal and Spain.
	   Three EU countries say they don't want to join, at least for
now: Britain, Denmark and Sweden.
	   One country failed to meet qualifying economic standards:
Greece.
</TEXT>
