<SLUG> BC-SCI-Mars-Name Contest,0196 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NASA seeking names for two soil-penetrating probes
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With SCI-US-Digging into Mars &QL; 
 &UR; By The Associated Press &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   NASA is holding a contest to name the twin soil-penetrating
probes to be launched Jan. 3 aboard the Mars Polar Lander.
	   The probes, formally known as Deep Space 2, can be named after
people, places or things from history, mythology or fiction. The
only catch: NASA wants the two names to relate to one another and
the people they're named after must be dead.
	   The names of explorers or pioneers are welcome, the names of
super heroes are not. So forget Batman and Robin.
	   Entries must be accompanied by an essay of no more than 100
words explaining why the names were chosen. The deadline is April
30, 1999.
	   Entry rules and forms are available at this Internet address:
http://nmp.jpl.nasa.gov/ds2/contest/index.html
	   Entries also can be mailed to: Deep Space 2 Naming Contest, Jet
Propulsion Laboratory, 4800 Oak Grove Drive, Mail Stop 301-235,
Pasadena, California. 91109-8099.
	   The grand prize has yet to be announced. All 25 finalists will
receive a Deep Space 2 poster signed by the project team.
</TEXT>
