w1495 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FEA-1998-Deaths 8thAdd   12-30 0332
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FEA-1998-Deaths, 8th Add,0331 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UNDATED: was 80
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Sept. 1
	   Lord Rothermere, the owner of the Daily Mail, the Mail on Sunday
and London's Evening Standard, dies of a heart attack in London. He
was 73.
	   Sept. 6
	   Akira Kurosawa, Japan's internationally known film director,
dies in Tokyo of a stroke. He was 88.
	   Sept. 7
	   Edward A. Weinstein, an author and neuropsychiatrist who
researched the interrelationship of brain function, culture and
experience, dies in Bethesda, Maryland. He was 89.
	   Ernest Ametistov, a member of Russia's highest court who
defended democratic freedoms and spearheaded legal reforms, dies at
his home near Moscow. He was 64.
	   Sept. 11
	   Ricardo Arnoldo Ramirez de Leon, a former leftist guerrilla
commander who signed peace accords with the Guatemalan government
in 1996, dies of a heart attack in Guatemala City, Guatemala. He
was 67.
	   Sept. 13
	   Antonio Nunez Jimenez, who fought alongside Che Guevara and went
on to hold top positions in the Cuban government, dies in Havana,
Cuba. He was 75.
	   Gov. George C. Wallace, the former Alabama governor who declared
``segregation forever,'' dies of respiratory and cardiac arrest in
Montgomery, Alabama. He was 79.
	   Sept. 15
	   Viljo Akseli Heino, the last of the great track stars known as
the ``Flying Finns,'' dies in Tampere, Finland. He was 84.
	   Sept. 18
	   Kurt Hager, the longtime chief ideologue of former East
Germany's Politburo, dies in Berlin. He was 86.
	   Sept. 21
	   Florence Griffith Joyner, a sprinter who won three gold medals
at the 1988 Olympics, is found dead at her home in Mission Viejo,
California, after a history of heart trouble. She was 38.
	   Sept. 29
	   Bruno Munari, an architect and artist who was a leading member
of Italy's futurist movement, dies in Milan, Italy. He was 90.
	   Sept. 30
	   Marius Goring, a British actor who played villainous Nazis on
the big screen, dies in West Sussex, England. He was 86.
 &UR; MORE
</TEXT>
